# Week 9 - Day 3: Celebrity Problem

## üìå Problem Statement

A celebrity is a person who:
- Is known by everyone.
- Does not know anyone.

Given a matrix `M` of size `n x n` where:
- `M[i][j] = 1` means person `i` knows person `j`
- `M[i][j] = 0` means person `i` does not know person `j`

Find the index of the celebrity. If no celebrity exists, return -1.

---

## üß† Approach (Stack Based ‚Äì Optimal O(N))

### Step 1: Push all people into a stack.
### Step 2: Pop two people A and B.
- If A knows B ‚Üí A cannot be celebrity.
- Else ‚Üí B cannot be celebrity.
Push the remaining candidate back.

Repeat until one candidate remains.

### Step 3: Verify the candidate:
- Row should be all 0s.
- Column should be all 1s except diagonal.

---

## ‚è±Ô∏è Time Complexity
- O(N)

## üì¶ Space Complexity
- O(N)

``cpp
  #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <stack>
using namespace std;
int celebraty(vector<vector<int>> mat)
{
    stack<int> s;
    for (int i = 0; i < mat.size(); i++)
    {
        s.push(i);
    }

    while (s.size() > 1)
    {
        int i = s.top();
        s.pop();

        int j = s.top();
        s.pop();

        if (mat[i][j] == 0)
        {
            s.push(i);
        }
        else
        {
            s.push(j);
        }
    }
    int celeb = s.top();
    for(int i=0;i<mat.size();i++){
        if((i!=celeb) && (mat[i][celeb]==0 || mat[celeb][i]==1)){
            return -1;
        }
    }
    return celeb;
}

int main()
{
    vector<vector<int>> mat = {{0, 1, 0},
                               {0, 0, 0},
                               {0, 1, 0}};

    int ans = celebraty(mat);
    cout << "celebraty is:" << ans;
    return 0;
}
